==English==

===Pronunciation===
*trī'-ăng-gəl, /ˈtraɪæŋɡəl/, /<tt>"traI{Ng@l</tt>/

===Noun===
'''triangle''' (''plural:'' '''[[triangles]]''')

#{{geometry}} A [[polygon]] with three sides and three angles.
#{{musici}} A [[percussion instrument]] made by forming a metal rod into a triangular shape which is open at one angle. It is suspended from a string and hit with a metal bar to make a [[resonant]] sound.
#(''snooker, pool, billiards etc.'') A triangular shaped piece of equipment used for gathering the balls into the formation required by the game being played. [[Category:Snooker]]
# A [[love triangle]].

====Synonyms====
*(''polygon''): [[trigon]] (''rare'')
*(''love triangle''): [[love triangle]], [[menage à trois]]

